Dialogue: 10,0:01:35.60,0:01:37.76,Top,,0,0,0,,Yippee, lessons are over!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:37.76,0:01:39.88,Top,,0,0,0,,Hey, shall we all go to the pictures?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:39.88,0:01:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The pictures, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:41.27,0:01:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if we should.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:42.90,0:01:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t you two have \Nrather more pressing business?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:46.39,0:01:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:47.54,0:01:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,O’Sullivan twins, \NHeadmistress wants to see you.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:51.40,0:01:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:03.26,0:02:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, whatever have you done this time \Nto get summoned by Headmistress?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:08.61,0:02:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It must've been you.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:10.23,0:02:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember when you gave \Nsuch a huge yawn during morning prayers?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:13.70,0:02:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So she wants to scold... {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:14.62,0:02:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... It's not that! Could it be...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:17.74,0:02:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,about Headmistress’s roses?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:25.36,0:02:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We are very sorry, Headmistress.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:29.10,0:02:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though we were on duty... {?? not sure what she means, probably that girls look after the orchard in turns?}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:31.72,0:02:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was only twice \Nthat we forgot to water your roses.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:37.59,0:02:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,N-No, it was closer to five times...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:40.36,0:02:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodness!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:41.63,0:02:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We're sorry!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:43.00,0:02:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Was that so? \NI didn’t know.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:45.85,0:02:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:47.44,0:02:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll have to take your punishment duty properly later. {meaning they'll be sent on that duty again as a punishment ig}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:50.47,0:02:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:51.17,0:02:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:53.97,0:02:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Today I had meant to bestow \Na great honour upon you both.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:59.25,0:03:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,An honour?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:00.81,0:03:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d like you two to represent us \Nat the National Speech Contest in London.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:07.32,0:03:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The National Speech Contest?!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:10.19,0:03:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The one where top pupils \Nfrom schools across the country compete?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:15.13,0:03:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And only those with excellent results, talent in sport \Nand outstanding character may enter?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:22.85,0:03:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,A-And you're sending us?!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:25.27,0:03:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I consulted both staff and pupils \Nat St. Clare’s about whom to choose.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:32.08,0:03:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:33.28,0:03:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But we recommended Hilary.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:36.38,0:03:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But Hilary insisted that you two should go.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:38.74,0:03:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:39.12,0:03:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet, Kathleen, \Nand all the teachers agreed as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:45.06,0:03:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But why?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:46.44,0:03:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, if we'd known about the roses \Nwe might have changed our minds!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:51.36,0:03:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We're sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:53.63,0:03:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps they thought the theme \N{of the speech }suited you two perfectly.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:57.80,0:03:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The theme?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:58.71,0:04:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“Our Dreams.”
Dialogue: 10,0:04:01.14,0:04:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“Our...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:02.31,0:04:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Dreams”?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:03.41,0:04:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I also think it’s a theme where your \Ncheerfulness and upbeat spirit will truly shine.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:10.05,0:04:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Patricia, Isabel,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:12.05,0:04:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,live up to the whole school’s expectations. \NGive a splendid speech at the contest.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:18.66,0:04:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:20.93,0:04:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yippee!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:24.43,0:04:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Fancy that—we’re to represent St. Clare’s!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:26.57,0:04:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What an incredible honour!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:28.17,0:04:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, twins!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:29.55,0:04:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:32.71,0:04:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:33.61,0:04:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, everyone.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:35.51,0:04:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s the first time twins have ever \Nbeen chosen as contestants, you know.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:39.11,0:04:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hooray for the twins! {/go, go, twins}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:43.57,0:04:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Hooray for the twins!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:50.99,0:04:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?! You two, the representatives for the National Speech Contest?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:57.35,0:04:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And with “Our Dreams” as the theme!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:59.77,0:05:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I feel that we can nail it! {?? lit: i have a feeling "Oh, just leave it to us." - think she means they're very confident}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:01.67,0:05:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting today we’ll write \Na brilliant draft together.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:04.57,0:05:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,See you!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:09.48,0:05:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:10.91,0:05:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Those mischievous girls, \Nchosen as St. Clare’s representatives?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:13.68,0:05:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,With “Our Dreams” as their subject.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:16.58,0:05:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what they’ll say.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:18.65,0:05:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever they’ve learnt during their time at St. Clare’s, their speech will lay it all out. {/bring to light}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:28.56,0:05:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“Our Dreams,” is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:30.53,0:05:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Dreams...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:31.90,0:05:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They sound simple, \Nbut can be rather difficult.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:34.14,0:05:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:35.70,0:05:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you writing your draft already?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:37.80,0:05:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:38.34,0:05:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Hilary, what’s your dream?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:41.41,0:05:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:42.41,0:05:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,To follow in my father’s footsteps, of course.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:44.81,0:05:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Right... As a teacher \Nat the school for the blind?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:47.98,0:05:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,At present, he’s translating \Nthe world’s classics into Braille.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:51.15,0:05:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:52.42,0:05:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,How marvellous!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:53.52,0:06:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The blind want to know and learn, too. \NMy dream is to help them in any way I can. {??? think she means "my dream is to avail them to that power from now on"}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:01.00,0:06:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:02.56,0:06:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And Kathleen, you want to be a vet?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:04.56,0:06:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I decided when I saved Binks’s life.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:08.07,0:06:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,A vet, no matter what.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:09.74,0:06:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There are so many animals \Non the brink of extinction right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:14.67,0:06:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to do work that will save their lives.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:19.08,0:06:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And me, I’ll be a judge! {judge; judiciary - I think...}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:20.78,0:06:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:21.58,0:06:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You, Joan?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:22.28,0:06:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,A judge?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:23.82,0:06:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Girls must go out into the world \Nand make their mark too.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:28.02,0:06:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,When I leave St. Clare’s,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:30.16,0:06:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll sit for the bar exam.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:47.54,0:06:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Brilliant, Gladys!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:49.38,0:06:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve cut your time again.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:51.58,0:06:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Nearly at the Olympics now.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:54.65,0:06:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:55.68,0:06:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:57.62,0:07:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll make my dream come true \Nby my own efforts, just you wait.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:04.62,0:07:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re all amazing.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:06.26,0:07:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They have real dreams, \Nand work so hard for them.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:10.43,0:07:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then look at us—\Nwe can’t think of anything.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:14.00,0:07:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We simply drift along day by day,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:16.84,0:07:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,never once thinking seriously about \Nwhat we want to do when we’re grown up.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:22.08,0:07:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s pathetic, really! \NAnd we're already fourteen!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:24.95,0:07:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:25.61,0:07:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, what have you been \Nstudying for every day? {lit: for the sake of what}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:29.42,0:07:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, really? \NWhat about you, then, Pat? {that naniyo is most likely "what kind of questions is that" - meaning she's slightly offended at it}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:31.75,0:07:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I... Well...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:33.89,0:07:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I said it before—\NI wanted to be an illustrator.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:37.19,0:07:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonsense! You gave that up the other day, \Nsaid you had no talent.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:40.73,0:07:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, I’ve talent for being a novelist.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:42.83,0:07:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m writing a detective story now. {/mystery}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:45.17,0:07:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Gave up after two pages, haven't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:48.20,0:07:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Your dreams never last more than a week.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:51.14,0:07:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That hardly counts as a real dream.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:53.57,0:07:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that so? {lit: you said it didn't you}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:54.98,0:07:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And what about you?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:56.74,0:07:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven’t forgotten, you know.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:58.55,0:07:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That time...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:00.91,0:08:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Children, what do you want to be \Nwhen you grow up?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:05.10,0:08:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Me! Pat wants to be a ballerina.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:08.52,0:08:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Then Isabel too, a ballerina.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:12.16,0:08:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Then Pat will be a policewoman.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:14.29,0:08:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Then Isabel too, a policewoman.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:17.93,0:08:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-That was ages ago!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:20.53,0:08:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But nothing’s changed now.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:23.27,0:08:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,"I don’t know what my dream is.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:25.44,0:08:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat doesn’t, so I don't know either!" {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:27.91,0:08:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You're so indecisive, \Nalways worrying about what others think.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:30.78,0:08:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you have a will of your own?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:32.81,0:08:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:33.98,0:08:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder no true dream \Ncan be born here.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:36.68,0:08:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How cruel! You’re always so pushy, \Nand I just have to go along with you.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:41.38,0:08:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:42.56,0:08:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a dream of my own.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:44.52,0:08:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,A far bigger dream than yours!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:47.60,0:08:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’ll not lose to the likes of you.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:50.33,0:08:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a genuine dream \Nno one else has ever thought of.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:56.04,0:08:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What, two separate drafts?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:59.11,0:09:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. We’ll split the ten minute limit \Nand each will give her own speech.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:04.71,0:09:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... Really...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:09.73,0:09:11.95,Thought,,0,0,0,,My own dream...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:18.04,0:09:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, a nurse!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:20.49,0:09:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve always rather admired them.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:22.40,0:09:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s it!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:35.78,0:09:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Isabel, is your draft coming along?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:38.31,0:09:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You're writing about nurses, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:41.21,0:09:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but... it’s no good.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:44.09,0:09:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t write it well at all.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:45.62,0:09:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t believe it! \NThe contest is tomorrow!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:48.69,0:09:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:49.49,0:09:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what about a barrister? {/advocate/lawyer/solicitor}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:50.89,0:09:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn’t feel right.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:52.36,0:09:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Then maybe Prime Minister, bold as you like? {lit: PM, with a bang - meaning "not be shy, go balls to the wall"}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:05.97,0:10:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:08.94,0:10:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You too, Isabel?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:10.84,0:10:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,My word, what on earth \Nare those twins going to do now?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:13.81,0:10:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If it comes to this, I shall...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:15.04,0:10:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Lewis!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:17.25,0:10:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave them be.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:18.79,0:10:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It is important for them to struggle as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:20.97,0:10:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But surely it is a teacher’s duty \Nto give some guidance to pupils in difficulty? {hint}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:25.73,0:10:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I have faith in the girls of St. Clare’s.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:29.20,0:10:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,As for Patricia and Isabel, in the end, \Nthey will surely find the answer for themselves.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:34.37,0:10:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If you wish to be a true educator, \Nyou too must learn to trust your pupils a little more.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:47.28,0:10:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, how goes it? {lit: what is the condition - dunno what to put here to connect it with "hai" next}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:49.68,0:10:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes…
Dialogue: 10,0:10:53.42,0:10:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All sorts of dreams keep coming to mind...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:56.16,0:10:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A nurse, a nursery teacher… {(female) childcare worker; nursery school teacher - think she means "mistress at the kindergarten"}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:58.76,0:11:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But when I ask myself why I want to be one,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:02.36,0:11:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t find the confidence.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:04.57,0:11:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So they’re not real dreams at all.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:07.57,0:11:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you’re thinking of dreams too grandly.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:12.41,0:11:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe what we call dreams \Nare something much closer to hand.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:16.38,0:11:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Closer to hand?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:18.25,0:11:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes—ordinary, honest dreams. {/down-to-earth/close to hand}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:21.88,0:11:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t bear it.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:27.02,0:11:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve been brooding so much, haven’t you?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:29.69,0:11:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t mean to pry, but it got me curious.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:34.16,0:11:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t understand.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:36.30,0:11:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t, for the life of me,\N discover what my dream is.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:39.97,0:11:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve thought and thought until my head aches, \Nyet nothing comes.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:43.30,0:11:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be because I have no \Nreal sense of responsibility as a person.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:47.34,0:11:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,To think I’m such a pitiful girl...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:51.53,0:11:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh dear—you’re in luck!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:53.76,0:11:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Wh-What do you mean?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:55.68,0:11:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, two eyes!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:01.56,0:12:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This joke is too old \Nfor your generation, it seems. {i didn't get it either}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:08.60,0:12:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,At any rate, if you wear such a gloomy face, \Nno dream will come to you.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:14.07,0:12:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:16.57,0:12:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold your heart large and open.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:18.77,0:12:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:20.81,0:12:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:21.84,0:12:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just like Mam’zelle. {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:23.14,0:12:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-confidence must be supple. {/resilient/bending}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:26.41,0:12:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:27.11,0:12:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a soft spring. {spring as in bounce, the device in mechanical devices, dunno it's clear enough}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:29.10,0:12:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Arrogant self-confidence snaps at once,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:32.65,0:12:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,but supple confidence makes a person \Nstrong all the way through. {/deep and strong}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:36.46,0:12:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If only you have that confidence in you, \Ndreams will come naturally.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:41.16,0:12:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally…
Dialogue: 10,0:12:42.70,0:12:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Right... I see now!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:45.07,0:12:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Mais, Pat... {??? doesn't sound like anything in japanese so idk what it could be}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:46.63,0:12:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oui, Mam’zelle?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:05.79,0:13:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,"That may have been my dream all along..."
Dialogue: 10,0:13:11.62,0:13:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,"My dream…
Dialogue: 10,0:13:14.08,0:13:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t yet know it clearly,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:17.46,0:13:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but if there’s one dream that's dearer to me than anything else, it’s Pat's. {lit: if there's only one dream that's close to me, that pat}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:22.50,0:13:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since I was little, \NI’ve been just a little jealous of her.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:26.17,0:13:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s so bright, so straightforward.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:27.86,0:13:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,While I… {/compared to her}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:30.24,0:13:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I fret too much about what others think, \Nrather than deciding for myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:35.75,0:13:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I could become a girl \Nwith Pat’s crisp, infinite energy.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:41.42,0:13:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That, perhaps, has been my dream."
Dialogue: 10,0:13:49.78,0:13:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What? You heard it?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:53.13,0:13:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Isabel,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:55.30,0:13:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,read this.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:56.15,0:13:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:57.79,0:14:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,"I have been envious of my \Ntwin sister Isabel from my childhood..." {copying from the onscreen text}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:02.76,0:14:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:04.11,0:14:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,"Because she is kind, calm, and honest. \NShe has plenty of character that I do not have. {clunky, but would look weird if we change it from the onscreen}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:09.52,0:14:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I am too quick a temper, and too rough a tongue, \Nand sometimes I hurt people unconsciously.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:17.99,0:14:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish to be the sort of person, \Nwho is warm and tolerant, just like Isabel. {can't read that word well, not sure it says tolerant}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:23.70,0:14:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That may be my dream."
Dialogue: 10,0:14:32.91,0:14:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I never knew you thought of me that way.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:36.18,0:14:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor did I know that about you.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:38.58,0:14:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Fourteen years together, \Nand still so oblivious...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:41.62,0:14:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,How silly we’ve been.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:49.96,0:14:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This won’t do for a proper \Npublic speech, though, will it? {lit: speech that you can let everyone hear}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:53.89,0:14:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Not until we find some more confidence \Nto speak of our true dreams...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:00.03,0:15:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Our true dreams?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:02.27,0:15:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Ordinary... {/Close to hand}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:03.54,0:15:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,honest dreams.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:05.44,0:15:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I know! Let’s just say it straight out.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:08.14,0:15:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:08.81,0:15:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:20.14,0:15:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“To become a natural scientist, \Nand safeguard the beauty of the earth—
Dialogue: 10,0:15:25.53,0:15:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that is my dream.”
Dialogue: 10,0:15:44.88,0:15:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how was that?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:46.78,0:15:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I got too tense, with the Crown Prince \Nand even the Lord Mayor of London present!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:52.55,0:15:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:55.12,0:15:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you truly going to give that speech?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:57.66,0:16:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They might throw us out of the hall for it!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:00.53,0:16:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,T-Take courage.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:02.70,0:16:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:04.03,0:16:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:04.95,0:16:07.00,Top,,0,0,0,,Next we have St. Clare’s School.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:07.00,0:16:11.79,Top,,0,0,0,,Patricia O’Sullivan, Isabel O’Sullivan—\Ntwin sisters, with their speech.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:14.72,0:16:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear…
Dialogue: 10,0:16:40.93,0:16:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:42.94,0:16:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,F-First, we must apologise to you all.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:46.57,0:16:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve not been able to find our dreams after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:50.58,0:16:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:52.63,0:16:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t know what our dreams are.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:55.88,0:16:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the honest truth.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:57.57,0:17:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If we ever had a dream... {one dream in life}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:00.24,0:17:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,it was to escape as quickly as we could\Nfrom that St. Clare’s School we loathed.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:08.60,0:17:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,U-Unbelievable!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:09.96,0:17:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What are they saying?!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:11.93,0:17:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What were they thinking, choosing those two \Nas the school's representatives?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:15.47,0:17:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:16.50,0:17:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not all! {????? definitely saying sometihng but fuck if i know}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:19.69,0:17:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,My, so clumsy!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:44.56,0:17:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Please—let them speak!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:48.95,0:17:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:50.00,0:17:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I know best of all why these two \Nwere chosen to represent St. Clare’s.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:56.28,0:18:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You see... I once stole money from a friend!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:00.78,0:18:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Stole?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:01.85,0:18:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:02.72,0:18:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Shameless!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:04.17,0:18:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was Pat and Isabel \Nwho first forgave me.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:09.69,0:18:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So gentle and considerate—to me, \Nwho had done something so base, {/vile}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:14.50,0:18:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,they gave the greatest treasure of all—friendship! {/presented me with the dearest treasure in the world}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:19.43,0:18:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I trust them.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:21.23,0:18:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And I!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:22.19,0:18:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Hilary…
Dialogue: 10,0:18:23.44,0:18:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,When my father fell ill \Nand I had no choice but to leave school,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:28.01,0:18:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat and Isabel did everything they could \Nand even more to let me stay till the very last.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:34.25,0:18:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They taught me so many things \Nnever written in any textbook.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:40.09,0:18:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:40.75,0:18:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:41.69,0:18:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We're with you! \NFear nothing! {??????? not a word}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:43.56,0:18:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,With supple confidence!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:45.26,0:18:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck, twins!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:46.76,0:18:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:51.66,0:18:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,When our parents first made us \Ncome to St. Clare’s,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:55.17,0:18:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,our only dream was indeed to run away.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:59.07,0:19:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, lo and behold, \Nforty-six miracles shattered that dream.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:04.88,0:19:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,One was Kathleen.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:07.55,0:19:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Always kind, always smiling \Nin the background—Kathleen! {?? literal, but not sure what she means, probably that she was out of the way, but always quietly was happy for the others}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:11.69,0:19:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But when someone was in trouble, \Na sudden, unexpected courage emerges in her.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:17.91,0:19:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,She amazed us time and again.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:21.09,0:19:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And Hilary.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:23.03,0:19:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Her character wins \Neveryone’s respect without effort. {/naturally}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:27.00,0:19:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Deeply emotive as a forest, warm as the sun.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:32.27,0:19:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet, so cheeky and stubborn, \Nis my eternal rival.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:36.48,0:19:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Joan, who could always laugh away \Nour sorrows, no matter how deep.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:40.88,0:19:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They, who gave us fresh energy \Nto carry on fighting— {?? dunno what to make of this yoshi yaruzotte, probably meaning "they'd always say 'all right, let's do it'"}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:44.45,0:19:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheila, Vera, Alison—our classmates.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:47.79,0:19:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And Headmistress.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:50.19,0:19:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We spoiled, selfish girls \Nnever trusted grown-ups.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:53.89,0:19:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet one glance into the Headmistress’s eyes and,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:57.60,0:20:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,as if by magic, we felt that we could be completely open with her. {sunao is an ambiguous word, could be "honest/docile/sincere" - I think she means "mysteriously, we felt like we can talk to headmistress about anything"}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:01.37,0:20:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The Headmistress has magical eyes.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:04.65,0:20:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And the teachers who laugh with us, \Nweep with us, and scold us when we need it...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:10.71,0:20:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,as people, and as women, \Nyou are shining examples to us.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:14.21,0:20:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We were moved time and again \Nby each and every one of you.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:18.25,0:20:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Each day felt like a miracle.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:20.92,0:20:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,To be learning at St. Clare’s—\Nthat is now our greatest pride.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:27.06,0:20:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We shall go on searching for our true dreams, \Nhesitating, struggling, failing, and trying again.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:36.90,0:20:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:37.50,0:20:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we have faith. {/confidence}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:39.41,0:20:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that dreams will be born here...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:41.11,0:20:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,At the wonderful school of St. Clare’s.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:43.58,0:20:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We feel the first shoots of those dreams \Nare already stirring within us even now.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:49.95,0:20:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,St. Clare’s is our soil, \Nnurturing the buds of our dreams. {? hope it's daichi and not daiichi}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:53.52,0:20:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And the tears, laughter, and encouragement of all forty-six of us, are the sun that shines upon them.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:59.96,0:21:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:00.69,0:21:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we hold our heads high.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:04.70,0:21:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,As we continue to walk towards dreams yet unknown,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:08.83,0:21:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,dreams that lie dormant deep in our hearts, \Nbut shall one day branch out,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:12.77,0:21:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,spreading far and wide! {had to turn the whole sentence around but would look ugly if I preserved the japanese order}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:41.97,0:21:43.89,Thought,,0,0,0,,Thank you, everyone.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:44.34,0:21:46.71,Thought,,0,0,0,,Thank you, St. Clare’s.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:47.24,0:21:49.58,Thought,,0,0,0,,Thank you, for everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.12,0:21:46.53,Song,,0,0,0,,I just stared out the window all through class,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.53,0:21:52.57,Song,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,500)}Always dreaming away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.10,0:22:00.51,Song,,0,0,0,,But if I'd at least taken English seriously,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.47,0:22:08.24,Song,,0,0,0,,By now I'd be some cool international girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.71,0:22:15.82,Song,,0,0,0,,Better to study while you still have the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.82,0:22:22.96,Song,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,2222)}Realizing too late won't help you then.
